<TITLE> Reconditioned cars may get cheaper </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)  The price of reconditioned cars may slightly fall on the back of the government proposal to increase dealers' commission discount rate. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam Thursday proposed a rise of the dealers' commission discount rate on used reconditioned cars from 25 percent to 30 percent. Abdul Haque, president of Bangladesh Reconditioned Vehicles Importers and Dealers Association, hailed the move as a positive decision. He thanked the adviser for his move to encourage the sector. He, however, feared the price of microbus would go up by Tk 4 to 6 lakh as the government has bracketed microbus in the tax structure on the basis of CC. It would hit the microbus users, he said. bdnew
